The Islamic militant group, Boko
Haram, threatened further attacks in  Nigeria  after saying it was
behind a suicide bombing at the police headquarters yesterday,
 ThisDay  reported, citing Usman Al-Zawahiri, a spokesman for the
group who spoke to the Voice of America.  The blast, which occurred in Abuja, the capital, killed at
least six people and injured 12 others, the Lagos-based
newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Elisha Bala-Gbogbo in Abuja at 
 ebalagbogbo@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 